Compiler Option: -d
===================

Add a preprocessor definition

Syntax:
-d < name=value >
-d < name >

Parameters:
`name`
Name of the preprocessor macro to define. No parameters are allowed.

`value`
Value to give to the macro. If omitted, it will be defined as 1

Description:
The `-d` compiler option adds a preprocessor macro to all source files. The
same as using the preprocessor directive `#define` or `#macro`.
